WEBVTT

00:07:27.116 --> 00:07:31.113
can be the first gauntlet we throw down
in a battle against oppression.

00:07:32.279 --> 00:07:33.465
And fashion --

00:07:33.926 --> 00:07:36.336
it can create visual disruption for us --

00:07:36.926 --> 00:07:38.316
on us, literally.

00:07:39.942 --> 00:07:42.521
Lessons of defiance
have always been taught

00:07:42.545 --> 00:07:44.518
by fashion's great revolutionaries:

00:07:45.045 --> 00:07:46.226
its designers.

00:07:47.041 --> 00:07:51.985
Jean Paul Gaultier taught us
that women can be kings.

00:07:52.718 --> 00:07:54.065
Thom Browne --

00:07:54.089 --> 00:07:56.906
he taught us that men can wear heels.

00:07:58.392 --> 00:08:02.847
And Alexander McQueen,
in his spring 1999 show,